The paper proposes a new method for mixture proportion estimation, which is a problem commonly studied in machine learning and statistics. The paper also discusses the limitations of existing methods and proposes a new approach that does not rely on the irreducible assumption. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), statistics (cs.ST), and information theory (cs.IT).
